        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-09-06T12:12:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-09-06T12:12:00-05:00" n="199"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                <head>199. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Soviet Union</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d199fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName
                            corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 330, Subject Files, Hijackings.
                        Confidential; Limited Official Use; Flash. Drafted and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_DRP1">Davies</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1970-09-06T17:12:00+00:00">September 6, 1970,
                        1712Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>146336. Three <gloss target="#t_US1">US</gloss> airliners have been hijacked by
                    Palestinian groups.<note n="2" xml:id="d199fn2">A fourth plane, El Al flight 219
                        flying from Amsterdam to New York City, was also hijacked by two people, but
                        El Al crew members shot and killed one hijacker and wounded the other.
                        (Memorandum for the Record, September 6; ibid.) For additional documentation
                        on this and subsequent hijackings on September 6, see <ref
                            target="frus1969-76ve01#d45">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1969–1976, volume E–1,
                            Documents on Global Issues, 1969–1972, Documents 45 ff</ref>.</note> You
                    should contact Foreign Ministry soonest and ask for Soviet intervention should
                    any of the flights land in Baghdad to the end that passenger, plane and crew are
                    promptly released. Flights involved are <gloss target="#t_TWA1">TWA</gloss> 741,
                    Pan American 093 and Pan American 3.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
